openaiSpec.name: get_weather
openaiSpec.description: Retrieve weather data for a specified location. Users can customize which weather variables to include based on their preferences.

count.description: The number of results to return for location searches. Adjust this value as necessary to find the correct location.

language.description: The language for the location search. Use ISO 639-1 two-letter language codes (e.g., 'en' for English, 'es' for Spanish).

location.description: The name of the location to search for. If a state is provided, spell out the full name (e.g., Texas instead of TX). The location is always treated as a city by default.

include_daily_weather.description: Include daily weather data in the response.

include_hourly_weather.description: Include hourly weather data in the response.

include_current_weather.description: Include current weather data in the response.

userSettings.name: current_weather
userSettings.label: Current Weather Variables (comma-separated)
userSettings.description: A comma-separated list of current weather variables to fetch. Default: 'temperature_2m,relative_humidity_2m,is_day,precipitation,wind_speed_10m,weather_code'.

userSettings.name: hourly_weather
userSettings.label: Hourly Weather Variables (comma-separated)
userSettings.description: A comma-separated list of hourly weather variables to fetch. Default: 'temperature_2m,relative_humidity_2m,precipitation_probability,wind_speed_10m,weather_code'.

userSettings.name: daily_weather
userSettings.label: Daily Weather Variables (comma-separated)
userSettings.description: A comma-separated list of daily weather variables to fetch. Default: 'weather_code,temperature_2m_max,temperature_2m_min,precipitation_probability_max'.

userSettings.name: temperature_unit
userSettings.label: Temperature Unit
userSettings.description: The unit of temperature to use. Default: 'fahrenheit'.

userSettings.name: timezone
userSettings.label: Timezone
userSettings.description: The timezone for the weather data. Default: 'auto'.
